reviews.text:
Kwong Kee Restaurant is a long history restaurant in the area, and they have a couple of famous dishes.
Most of their food are great, if you don't know the best one, you can simple ask the owner help for on your order.  Just tell her how many people to serve, and she will prepare the dishes well fit to the customers.
As the restaurant is old, don't expect the restaurant will be very new or clean
Home style cooking and hospitality at its finest. All the produce is very fresh and the seasoning is perfect. Restaurant that's full of regulars. What a great find tonight!
Super yummy. Simple yet very tasty local food. Must eat the lamb pot with the fermented bean curb sauce.
Incredible sweet and sour pork.
Nice local food. Friendly services. Much better than any chain stores.
